    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="currently-oct-2016-there-are-more-then-60-sbcs-with-open-specification-and-this-number-is-growing-fast">Currently (Oct 2016) there are more then 60 SBCs<sup class="footnote-ref"><a href="#fn1" id="fnref1">[1]</a></sup> with open-specification and this number is growing fast!</h3>
<p>this is our subjective rank on SBCs (Single Board Computers)</p>
<a id="more"></a>
<p>For our project’s needs, we have looked at almost all available for purchase single-board computers. We have checked if they were:</p>
<ul>
<li>hacker friendly</li>
<li>Linux compatible</li>
<li>open-spec</li>
<li>low-cost</li>
<li>effective</li>
</ul>
<p>According to our internal magic score algorithm, C.H.I.P., Raspberry Pi (especially model zero), and Orange Pi (especially model PC+) have the higher price-performance ratio.</p>
